'''基因重配'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.termonline.cn/search?k=reassortment |title=存档副本 |access-date=2021-08-04 |archive-date=2021-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210804093952/https://www.termonline.cn/search?k=reassortment }}</ref> （英文：Reassortment）是指某个[[物种|物种]]的[[遗传学|遗传材料]]之间相互混合，在物种的不同个体中形成新的组合的现象。基因重配的过程包括[[染色体|染色体]]重组、[[染色體互換|染色体互换]]等，也可能是两个相似[[病毒|病毒]]在感染同一个[[细胞|细胞]]的时候进行了遗传材料交换。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Reassortment in segmented RNA viruses: mechanisms and outcomes|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/nrmicro.2016.46|last=McDonald|first=Sarah M.|last2=Nelson|first2=Martha I.|date=2016-07|journal=Nature Reviews Microbiology|issue=7|doi=10.1038/nrmicro.2016.46|volume=14|pages=448–460|language=en|issn=1740-1534|last3=Turner|first3=Paul E.|last4=Patton|first4=John T.|access-date=2021-01-05|archive-date=2022-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521155251/https://www.nature.com/articles/nrmicro.2016.46}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=RNA Virus Reassortment: An Evolutionary Mechanism for Host Jumps and Immune Evasion|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4497687/|last=Vijaykrishna|first=Dhanasekaran|last2=Mukerji|first2=Reshmi|date=2015-07-09|journal=PLoS Pathogens|issue=7|doi=10.1371/journal.ppat.1004902|volume=11|issn=1553-7366|pmc=4497687|pmid=26158697|last3=Smith|first3=Gavin J. D.|access-date=2021-01-05|archive-date=2020-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105161757/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4497687/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

基因重配常发生于[[流感病毒|流感病毒]]中。[[甲型流感病毒|甲型]]、[[乙型流感病毒|乙型流感病毒]]拥有8个不同的[[RNA|RNA]]片段、丙型拥有7个RNA片段，有如小型的染色体。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=THE BIOLOGY OF INFLUENZA VIRUSES|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3074182/|last=Bouvier|first=Nicole M.|last2=Palese|first2=Peter|date=2008-09-12|journal=Vaccine|issue=Suppl 4|volume=26|pages=D49–D53|issn=0264-410X|pmc=3074182|pmid=19230160|access-date=2021-01-05|archive-date=2022-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324021240/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3074182/}}</ref> 当病毒进行组装时，每个片段都会被复制一段。当某个宿主（人，鸡，或其他动物）同时感染了两种或以上不同流感病毒时，新组装的病毒颗粒就可能同时包含之前不同病毒的RNA片段。新的重排毒株会体现出原始毒株的部分特性。

历史上一些重大的流感大流行就与流感病毒的基因重配有关。比如1968-69年的“[[香港流感|香港流感]]”[[H3N2|H3N2]]病毒就是来自于1957-58年的“[[亚洲流感|亚洲流感]]”[[H2N2|H2N2]]病毒的基因重配（[[抗原转变|抗原转变]]）<ref>{{Cite web|title=1968 Pandemic (H3N2 virus) {{!}} Pandemic Influenza (Flu) {{!}} CDC|url=https://www.cdc.gov/flu/pandemic-resources/1968-pandemic.html|accessdate=2021-01-05|date=2019-01-22|work=www.cdc.gov|language=en-us|archive-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204073412/https://www.cdc.gov/flu/pandemic-resources/1968-pandemic.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Influenza A Virus (H2N2) - an overview|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/biochemistry-genetics-and-molecular-biology/influenza-a-virus-h2n2|accessdate=2021-01-05|author=|date=|format=|work=|publisher=ScienceDirect Topics|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208235043/https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/biochemistry-genetics-and-molecular-biology/influenza-a-virus-h2n2|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而[[2009年H1N1流感大流行|2009年流感大流行]]中的[[H1N1|H1N1]]流感病毒同时包含有[[猪|猪]]、[[禽类|禽类]]和人类流感病毒的基因序列。<ref name="NewSci-20090424-pandemic2">{{cite news|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17025-deadly-new-flu-virus-in-us-and-mexico-may-go-pandemic.html|title=Deadly new flu virus in US and Mexico may go pandemic|work=[[New_Scientist|New Scientist]]|date=2009-04-24|accessdate=2009-04-26|archive-date=2009-04-28|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5gNd9HTT9?url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17025-deadly-new-flu-virus-in-us-and-mexico-may-go-pandemic.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 感染[[蛇|蛇]]的[[沙粒病毒科|沙粒病毒科]]中，由于基因重配，也出现了高度的[[基因多样性|基因多样性]]。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Widespread recombination, reassortment, and transmission of unbalanced compound viral genotypes in natural arenavirus infections|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25993603/|last=Stenglein|first=Mark D.|last2=Jacobson|first2=Elliott R.|date=2015-05|journal=PLoS pathogens|issue=5|doi=10.1371/journal.ppat.1004900|volume=11|pages=e1004900|issn=1553-7374|pmc=4438980|pmid=25993603|last3=Chang|first3=Li-Wen|last4=Sanders|first4=Chris|last5=Hawkins|first5=Michelle G.|last6=Guzman|first6=David S.-M.|last7=Drazenovich|first7=Tracy|last8=Dunker|first8=Freeland|last9=Kamaka|first9=Elizabeth K.|access-date=2021-01-05|archive-date=2021-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108170520/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25993603/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

